WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:07.764 --> 00:00:11.398
♪ Edelweiss. edelweiss

2
00:00:12.531 --> 00:00:17.198
♪ Small and white

3
00:00:17.231 --> 00:00:21.398
♪ Clean and bright

4
00:00:21.431 --> 00:00:30.464
♪ Blossom of snow. may you bloom and grow ♪

5
00:00:30.498 --> 00:00:39.164
♪ Bloom and grow forever

6
00:00:39.198 --> 00:00:47.398
♪ Edelweiss. edelweiss

7
00:00:47.431 --> 00:00:56.898
♪ Bless my homeland forever

8
00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:04.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

9
00:01:40.898 --> 00:01:42.231
Aah!

10
00:03:01.117 --> 00:03:02.831
Couldn't sleep?

11
00:03:04.386 --> 00:03:05.786
No.

12
00:03:06.852 --> 00:03:09.386
Me. either.

13
00:03:09.419 --> 00:03:11.552
Is your room okay?

14
00:03:11.586 --> 00:03:14.052
I'm going to find a way to pay you back.

15
00:03:14.086 --> 00:03:16.352
Don't worry about it.

16
00:03:23.019 --> 00:03:24.552
Feel like a drive?

17
00:03:24.586 --> 00:03:26.086
Where to?

18
00:03:29.552 --> 00:03:31.586
Suspicious. aren't you?

19
00:04:14.886 --> 00:04:16.319
I drove it on the way in.

20
00:04:17.619 --> 00:04:19.952
Wow.

21
00:04:19.986 --> 00:04:22.586
Yeah. you don't get sunrises
like this back in Manhattan.

22
00:04:24.052 --> 00:04:25.319
No.

23
00:05:25.886 --> 00:05:27.952
Not really a sunrise diner. is it?

24
00:05:27.986 --> 00:05:29.519
I guess not.

25
00:05:32.019 --> 00:05:33.552
So I do have one question for you.

26
00:05:33.586 --> 00:05:35.986
What's that?

27
00:05:36.019 --> 00:05:38.486
Is there a Mr. Trudy?

28
00:05:39.719 --> 00:05:40.686
There's a Frank.

29
00:05:40.719 --> 00:05:41.752
Is he your husband?

30
00:05:41.786 --> 00:05:43.586
That's two questions.

31
00:05:45.119 --> 00:05:47.752
My turn.

32
00:05:47.786 --> 00:05:49.419
What's a guy like you
doing driving a truck?

33
00:05:49.452 --> 00:05:50.919
Ask me something else.

34
00:05:55.519 --> 00:05:57.752
I'm just following my father's footsteps.

35
00:05:59.086 --> 00:06:00.919
What would you like to do?

36
00:06:00.952 --> 00:06:02.519
That's two questions.

37
00:06:05.786 --> 00:06:07.452
What do you mean?

38
00:06:07.486 --> 00:06:09.886
With your life.

39
00:06:09.919 --> 00:06:10.952
If you could do anything.

40
00:06:10.986 --> 00:06:12.619
But I can't.

41
00:06:12.652 --> 00:06:14.752
Come on.

42
00:06:14.786 --> 00:06:16.119
Honestly?

43
00:06:16.152 --> 00:06:17.086
Yeah.

44
00:06:19.686 --> 00:06:21.052
Just about anything else.

45
00:06:29.386 --> 00:06:30.652
Thanks for the sunrise.

46
00:06:30.686 --> 00:06:31.919
Where are you going?

47
00:06:31.952 --> 00:06:33.852
To pay you back.

48
00:06:34.919 --> 00:06:36.319
Wish me luck.

49
00:06:56.819 --> 00:06:57.852
Good morning.

50
00:06:58.919 --> 00:06:59.986
If you want to eat.

51
00:07:00.019 --> 00:07:01.652
you got to pay first.

52
00:07:01.686 --> 00:07:03.986
Sign in the window says
you need a waitress.

53
00:07:06.652 --> 00:07:07.986
You planning on staying here?

54
00:07:08.019 --> 00:07:11.686
I don't know. but I could use a job.

55
00:07:12.819 --> 00:07:13.952
I'll think about it.

56
00:07:15.419 --> 00:07:16.686
What's thereto think about?

57
00:07:16.719 --> 00:07:18.786
You got a job. and I need one.

58
00:07:18.819 --> 00:07:22.819
Announcer on TV: Let's all
play "Guess My Game."

59
00:07:24.952 --> 00:07:27.752
Mr. Blake. a call came in for you.

60
00:07:27.786 --> 00:07:28.819
When?

61
00:07:28.852 --> 00:07:31.086
A few minutes ago.No message.

62
00:07:31.119 --> 00:07:32.686
First the popular columnist
whose "Voice of Broadway"

63
00:07:32.719 --> 00:07:34.719
appears in papers coast to coast:

64
00:07:34.752 --> 00:07:36.619
Miss Dorothy Dixon.

65
00:07:36.652 --> 00:07:38.619
Thank you. ladies and gentlemen.

66
00:07:38.652 --> 00:07:40.586
I normally don't introduce anyone

67
00:07:40.619 --> 00:07:42.752
who's shorter than myself. but--

68
00:07:50.019 --> 00:07:51.786
Can you bring the bacon in. please. Amy?

69
00:07:51.819 --> 00:07:52.986
Yes. Mommy.

70
00:07:54.786 --> 00:07:56.419
Very good. Thank you.

71
00:07:56.452 --> 00:07:57.813
Which way do the knives go. Jenny?

72
00:08:02.719 --> 00:08:05.486
So what shall we do after school today?

73
00:08:06.786 --> 00:08:08.119
Good morning. Mother.

74
00:08:08.152 --> 00:08:09.119
Good morning. Thomas.

75
00:08:09.152 --> 00:08:10.552
Good morning.

76
00:08:10.586 --> 00:08:13.019
- Coffee?
- Thank you.

77
00:08:16.486 --> 00:08:18.386
We all ready for the day ahead?

78
00:08:18.419 --> 00:08:20.020
- Yes. Father.
- Yes. Father.- Yes. Papa.

79
00:08:20.052 --> 00:08:21.619
Then why is your textbook open

80
00:08:21.652 --> 00:08:23.019
at the breakfast table. Thomas?

81
00:08:23.052 --> 00:08:25.786
Um. sorry. Father.

82
00:08:25.819 --> 00:08:26.786
I have a test today.

83
00:08:26.819 --> 00:08:28.719
Did you study last night?

84
00:08:28.752 --> 00:08:29.786
I did.

85
00:08:31.152 --> 00:08:33.986
It's just there's this boy Randolph.

86
00:08:34.019 --> 00:08:36.552
I don't want him to get the high score.

87
00:08:36.586 --> 00:08:38.052
Competition is healthy.

88
00:08:38.086 --> 00:08:40.052
He's just so annoying.

89
00:08:40.086 --> 00:08:43.452
He wears his hair past his collar

90
00:08:43.486 --> 00:08:45.719
and challenges teachers in class.

91
00:08:45.752 --> 00:08:47.352
Nonconformist.

92
00:08:47.386 --> 00:08:48.352
And proud of it.

93
00:08:48.386 --> 00:08:49.519
He makes negative comments

94
00:08:49.552 --> 00:08:50.719
about the school all the time.

95
00:08:50.752 --> 00:08:54.586
Why do you want to succeed. son?

96
00:08:56.386 --> 00:08:58.552
Why do you want to do well in school?

97
00:09:04.752 --> 00:09:06.452
To make my family proud.

98
00:09:07.686 --> 00:09:10.319
To bring honor to my school.

99
00:09:11.419 --> 00:09:12.719
To serve my country.

100
00:09:12.752 --> 00:09:15.519
Your goals are directed outward.

101
00:09:15.552 --> 00:09:18.786
A boy like Randolph

102
00:09:18.819 --> 00:09:20.919
wants only to gratify himself.

103
00:09:20.952 --> 00:09:24.552
This is the path to moral decay.

104
00:09:24.586 --> 00:09:28.819
The decadence ruined this
country before the war.

105
00:09:28.852 --> 00:09:32.619
You will grow to be a
useful member of society.

106
00:09:32.652 --> 00:09:34.752
You will make our nation stronger.

107
00:09:34.786 --> 00:09:36.686
Randolph will not.

108
00:09:36.719 --> 00:09:39.486
whatever his test score.

109
00:09:39.519 --> 00:09:41.752
Your father's a wise man. son.

110
00:09:44.719 --> 00:09:46.586
You may study at the
breakfast table. Thomas.

111
00:09:47.719 --> 00:09:49.952
Just this morning.

112
00:09:49.986 --> 00:09:51.719
Thank you. Father.

113
00:09:53.119 --> 00:09:54.352
Excuse me.

114
00:10:07.052 --> 00:10:08.652
Yes?

115
00:10:08.686 --> 00:10:09.652
You called?

116
00:10:09.686 --> 00:10:11.419
Where were you. Joe?

117
00:10:11.452 --> 00:10:13.786
I. uh. couldn't sleep.

118
00:10:13.819 --> 00:10:15.586
I went for a drive.

119
00:10:15.619 --> 00:10:17.852
Has your contact approached you?

120
00:10:19.652 --> 00:10:20.786
No. not yet.

121
00:10:20.819 --> 00:10:23.019
He must be assessing you.

122
00:10:23.052 --> 00:10:25.752
make sure you're not a Nazi agent.

123
00:10:25.786 --> 00:10:29.519
We received intelligence this morning.

124
00:10:29.552 --> 00:10:33.086
We believe a courier is carrying
some cargo from San Francisco.

125
00:10:33.119 --> 00:10:34.686
Okay. what's his name?

126
00:10:34.719 --> 00:10:37.852
It's a woman. not a man.

127
00:10:37.886 --> 00:10:40.652
Now. we don't know if she's
headed to Canon City.

128
00:10:40.686 --> 00:10:42.852
but you're to report in
immediately if you see her.

129
00:10:49.786 --> 00:10:51.619
Is she carrying a film. too?

130
00:10:54.386 --> 00:10:56.386
Who said you were carrying a film?

131
00:10:56.419 --> 00:10:57.752
I checked the cargo.

132
00:10:57.786 --> 00:10:58.886
I wanted to make sure it was safe.

133
00:10:58.919 --> 00:11:02.852
Joe. those weren’t your orders.

134
00:11:02.886 --> 00:11:05.886
I'm sorry. sir.

135
00:11:05.919 --> 00:11:07.852
But what's so important about a film?

136
00:11:07.886 --> 00:11:10.119
It's not your place to ask questions. Joe.

137
00:11:10.152 --> 00:11:13.352
Satisfy yourself with following orders.

138
00:11:13.386 --> 00:11:14.619
Understand?

139
00:11:16.052 --> 00:11:18.719
Yes. Obergruppenführer.

140
00:11:18.752 --> 00:11:22.052
You're performing a great
service for the Fatherland.

141
00:11:22.086 --> 00:11:23.686
Heil Hitler.

142
00:11:31.819 --> 00:11:35.052
No. No.

143
00:12:13.819 --> 00:12:16.852
Why aren't you circumcised. Mr. Frink?

144
00:12:16.886 --> 00:12:18.852
Why-- Why would I be?

145
00:12:18.886 --> 00:12:19.967
We've examined the records.

146
00:12:19.986 --> 00:12:22.052
Your grandfather Sheldon Frink--

147
00:12:22.086 --> 00:12:23.552
My grandmother was Christian.

148
00:12:23.586 --> 00:12:24.952
So were my mother and father.

149
00:12:24.986 --> 00:12:27.552
Jews don't get to decide if they're Jews.

150
00:12:27.586 --> 00:12:30.652
Not that I care.

151
00:12:30.686 --> 00:12:33.486
There are no Jews in Japan. after all.

152
00:12:33.519 --> 00:12:35.819
But our racial laws are now
aligned with the Reich.

153
00:12:35.852 --> 00:12:39.952
so it's not just you who
should be exterminated

154
00:12:39.986 --> 00:12:43.786
but also your sister Laura
and her children. too.

155
00:12:53.386 --> 00:12:54.852
You can't.

156
00:12:54.886 --> 00:12:56.519
The law is the law.

157
00:12:56.552 --> 00:12:59.519
Please. Please.

158
00:12:59.552 --> 00:13:03.486
I'm-- I'm begging you. please. Please.

159
00:13:07.552 --> 00:13:12.852
I could overlook this
if you cooperate fully.

160
00:13:12.886 --> 00:13:14.986
Yeah. yeah.

161
00:13:15.019 --> 00:13:18.719
All right. I. uh...

162
00:13:18.752 --> 00:13:20.032
What is it? What is it you want?

163
00:13:24.652 --> 00:13:26.119
You know what I want.

164
00:13:26.152 --> 00:13:27.686
The film.

165
00:13:27.719 --> 00:13:30.752
Trudy Walker gave it to your girlfriend.

166
00:13:30.786 --> 00:13:32.819
who has now fled.

167
00:13:32.852 --> 00:13:35.519
Where is Juliana Crain?

168
00:13:55.986 --> 00:13:57.386
Carl. thank you.

169
00:13:57.419 --> 00:13:58.852
- Thank you.
- Have a good day.

170
00:14:07.552 --> 00:14:09.652
Man: Miss?

171
00:14:09.686 --> 00:14:11.386
Miss?

172
00:14:19.019 --> 00:14:20.986
Here you go.

173
00:14:21.019 --> 00:14:22.819
What are you reading?

174
00:14:23.919 --> 00:14:25.386
You don't know what this is?

175
00:14:26.552 --> 00:14:27.586
Should I?

176
00:14:27.619 --> 00:14:28.686
It's a Bible.

177
00:14:28.719 --> 00:14:30.452
I haven't seen one of those

178
00:14:30.486 --> 00:14:32.352
since I was a little girl.

179
00:14:32.386 --> 00:14:33.752
Take a look.

180
00:14:37.086 --> 00:14:38.986
Hmm.

181
00:14:39.019 --> 00:14:40.652
Lighter than I remember.

182
00:14:40.686 --> 00:14:42.119
King James translation.

183
00:14:42.152 --> 00:14:44.086
He preferred small print.

184
00:14:48.652 --> 00:14:50.686
Those are forbidden in the Pacific States.

185
00:14:50.719 --> 00:14:51.986
The Reich. too.

186
00:14:53.386 --> 00:14:55.019
How'd you get it?

187
00:14:55.052 --> 00:14:56.752
You can find a lot of interesting things

188
00:14:56.786 --> 00:14:58.019
in the Neutral Zone.

189
00:14:58.052 --> 00:15:00.019
Don't you think?

190
00:15:36.452 --> 00:15:39.386
Japanese women aren't easily discouraged.

191
00:15:39.419 --> 00:15:41.352
They slam at those steel monsters

192
00:15:41.386 --> 00:15:42.786
as though they were beating
up their husbands.

193
00:15:44.619 --> 00:15:46.486
Do something. do something.
Say. that's a good idea.

194
00:15:46.519 --> 00:15:48.719
Maybe I can do something. Sure. Whoo-hoo!

195
00:15:54.886 --> 00:15:57.786
Man: It was 9:17 AM. Monday
the fourth of October.

196
00:15:57.819 --> 00:16:00.786
Detectives Foreman and Decker
investigating for the Reich police.

197
00:16:00.819 --> 00:16:02.619
4.000 marks had been reported missing

198
00:16:02.652 --> 00:16:05.619
from the payroll at 123
Street Agricultural Trust.

199
00:16:05.652 --> 00:16:07.086
Woman: How can I help you. detective?

200
00:16:07.119 --> 00:16:08.819
I was just getting ready for work.

201
00:16:08.852 --> 00:16:11.452
Man: And do you keep this
drawer locked. ma'am?

202
00:16:11.486 --> 00:16:14.452
Woman: Oh. I see. How silly of me.

203
00:16:14.486 --> 00:16:17.619
A lock's not much good if just
about anyone has access and a key.

204
00:16:17.652 --> 00:16:19.019
Man: Yes. ma'am.

205
00:16:19.052 --> 00:16:20.386
Woman: But who would do such a thing?

206
00:16:20.419 --> 00:16:21.852
Stealing money from the trust.

207
00:16:21.886 --> 00:16:22.852
that's like stealing from the Reich itself.

208
00:16:25.986 --> 00:16:27.586
Man #2: Stay back. you dumb cop!

209
00:16:27.619 --> 00:16:29.786
I'm through with your Reich lies!

210
00:16:31.152 --> 00:16:33.619
I want Foreman here. and I want him now!

211
00:16:33.652 --> 00:16:35.652
Or this dippy dough-head gets it!

212
00:16:46.686 --> 00:16:47.819
We are grateful to you

213
00:16:47.852 --> 00:16:49.486
for agreeing to this meeting.

214
00:16:49.519 --> 00:16:51.486
We want to ensure nothing disrupts

215
00:16:51.519 --> 00:16:53.652
the visit of the crown prince
and princess tomorrow.

216
00:16:53.686 --> 00:16:55.486
I believe everything is in hand.

217
00:16:55.519 --> 00:16:57.019
What is your concern. Ambassador?

218
00:16:59.152 --> 00:17:01.719
We understand you've arrested suspects

219
00:17:01.752 --> 00:17:03.386
smuggling subversive films.

220
00:17:03.419 --> 00:17:06.852
ones produced by the so-called
Man In the High Castle

221
00:17:06.886 --> 00:17:08.086
before his death.

222
00:17:08.119 --> 00:17:09.652
We've heard rumors

223
00:17:09.686 --> 00:17:11.486
the Man In the High Castle is still alive.

224
00:17:11.519 --> 00:17:14.119
No. he's dead. We've known for some months.

225
00:17:14.152 --> 00:17:15.752
We understand a fourth suspect

226
00:17:15.786 --> 00:17:16.952
fled with the films they were smuggling.

227
00:17:16.986 --> 00:17:18.419
A woman.

228
00:17:18.452 --> 00:17:20.886
You seem very well informed.

229
00:17:20.919 --> 00:17:22.752
Oberführer Diels.

230
00:17:22.786 --> 00:17:24.652
What else do you wish to know?

231
00:17:24.686 --> 00:17:27.719
Uh. we assume she fled to the Neutral Zone.

232
00:17:27.752 --> 00:17:29.719
We need to know where precisely.

233
00:17:29.752 --> 00:17:32.352
We are making inquiries.

234
00:17:32.386 --> 00:17:35.119
The Führer has decreed these
films be confiscated.

235
00:17:35.152 --> 00:17:38.086
Let me speak plainly. Tagomi-san.

236
00:17:38.119 --> 00:17:40.852
If you don't find this woman. we will.

237
00:17:44.519 --> 00:17:47.352
Duly acknowledged. Ambassador.

238
00:17:49.652 --> 00:17:53.819
But. respectfully. gentlemen.

239
00:17:53.852 --> 00:17:57.819
please be aware you’re on Japanese soil.

240
00:17:57.852 --> 00:18:03.552
We recognize the sovereignty of
the Pacific States. Minister.

241
00:18:03.586 --> 00:18:06.019
but this is a matter of state security.

242
00:18:06.052 --> 00:18:07.452
Good day. gentlemen.

243
00:18:30.119 --> 00:18:31.686
Check. please.

244
00:18:37.552 --> 00:18:38.919
3 marks.

245
00:18:40.719 --> 00:18:42.519
Here you go.

246
00:18:42.552 --> 00:18:44.719
You know what I was reading just now?

247
00:18:46.552 --> 00:18:48.552
The Book of Ecclesiastes.

248
00:18:48.586 --> 00:18:49.852
Oh. yeah?

249
00:18:49.886 --> 00:18:52.786
It says all life under the sun is futile.

250
00:18:52.819 --> 00:18:53.886
pointless.

251
00:18:53.919 --> 00:18:55.786
so we should dedicate our life

252
00:18:55.819 --> 00:18:57.419
to what's beyond the sun.

253
00:18:58.986 --> 00:19:00.852
Sounds interesting.

254
00:19:00.886 --> 00:19:02.652
What's beyond the sun?

255
00:19:04.486 --> 00:19:07.786
The Japanese say it's the emperor himself.

256
00:19:07.819 --> 00:19:10.519
beyond which there's only
duty to one's country.

257
00:19:10.552 --> 00:19:12.419
Self-sacrifice.

258
00:19:12.452 --> 00:19:13.886
And the Nazis?

259
00:19:15.419 --> 00:19:16.986
They say there's nothing at all.

260
00:19:17.019 --> 00:19:18.519
What do you say?

261
00:19:18.552 --> 00:19:21.519
Chapter 12. verse 5.

262
00:19:26.052 --> 00:19:28.486
You can pick up a copy at the bookstore.

263
00:19:40.852 --> 00:19:42.452
Raeder: You spoke to Joe
Blake this morning.

264
00:19:42.486 --> 00:19:43.952
Smith: I did.

265
00:19:43.986 --> 00:19:46.486
He should have been contacted by now.

266
00:19:46.519 --> 00:19:49.019
Well. it appears his contact is being
cautious.

267
00:19:50.552 --> 00:19:52.386
You don't think they suspect him.

268
00:19:52.419 --> 00:19:53.352
They suspect everyone.

269
00:19:55.386 --> 00:19:57.552
Steady. Erich.

270
00:19:57.586 --> 00:19:58.852
The bigger the fish.

271
00:19:58.886 --> 00:20:00.886
the greater the patience to catch it.

272
00:20:00.919 --> 00:20:02.552
This so-called Man In the High Castle.

273
00:20:02.586 --> 00:20:03.852
Reich Minister Goebbels says

274
00:20:03.886 --> 00:20:06.052
that not even Fraulein Riefenstahl

275
00:20:06.086 --> 00:20:07.819
could make films of such sophistication.

276
00:20:07.852 --> 00:20:09.686
If he made them.

277
00:20:09.719 --> 00:20:11.119
I don't understand.

278
00:20:11.152 --> 00:20:12.719
If he didn't. who did?

279
00:20:18.019 --> 00:20:20.052
I've heard strange rumors.

280
00:20:20.086 --> 00:20:21.552
Rumors?

281
00:20:21.586 --> 00:20:23.386
That the Führer considers the films

282
00:20:23.419 --> 00:20:26.386
a threat to the very
existence of the Reich.

283
00:20:26.419 --> 00:20:27.939
That's why he's so obsessed with them.

284
00:20:29.619 --> 00:20:31.619
Preposterous. isn't it?

285
00:20:31.652 --> 00:20:33.886
The Führer is not inclined
to idle obsession.

286
00:20:38.552 --> 00:20:39.886
Down!

287
00:20:46.119 --> 00:20:47.452
Man: Reload!

288
00:20:47.486 --> 00:20:50.519
Man: Is he dead?

289
00:21:31.152 --> 00:21:35.086
- Over here!
- Circle round! Circle round!

290
00:21:37.852 --> 00:21:38.786
Shit.

291
00:21:40.986 --> 00:21:43.519
Come on. Go!

292
00:22:21.386 --> 00:22:22.619
Hey. Ed.

293
00:22:28.052 --> 00:22:30.052
Mr. Windham-Matson. sir.

294
00:22:30.086 --> 00:22:31.686
Hey. good morning. Ed.
How's your grandfather?

295
00:22:31.719 --> 00:22:32.886
He's fine. sir. thank you.

296
00:22:32.919 --> 00:22:35.086
That should have two more cases on it.

297
00:22:35.119 --> 00:22:36.486
What can I help you with?

298
00:22:36.519 --> 00:22:38.119
It's Frank Frink. sir.

299
00:22:38.152 --> 00:22:39.652
I was wondering if he phoned in sick today.

300
00:22:39.686 --> 00:22:41.552
No. he hasn't.

301
00:22:41.586 --> 00:22:44.386
It's just that his phone doesn't pick up.

302
00:22:44.419 --> 00:22:47.352
Do you mind if I check to see if he's okay?

303
00:22:47.386 --> 00:22:48.752
You can dock my pay. of course.

304
00:22:48.786 --> 00:22:50.119
Go on.

305
00:22:50.152 --> 00:22:51.919
Thank you. sir.

306
00:22:51.952 --> 00:22:53.519
And don't worry.I will!

307
00:23:01.486 --> 00:23:02.286
Frank.

308
00:23:06.152 --> 00:23:09.052
Frank.Is that your name?

309
00:23:11.886 --> 00:23:13.086
Over here.

310
00:23:28.452 --> 00:23:29.852
It's okay. I'm a friend.

311
00:23:29.886 --> 00:23:32.619
I gave that film to Trudy Walker.

312
00:23:32.652 --> 00:23:34.719
Then you're definitely not a friend.

313
00:23:34.752 --> 00:23:38.052
You got to tell them I have
nothing to do with this.

314
00:23:38.086 --> 00:23:39.786
I'd save you if I could.

315
00:23:39.819 --> 00:23:41.452
I can't.

316
00:23:52.786 --> 00:23:54.752
Who the hell are you?

317
00:23:54.786 --> 00:23:56.986
A man. just like you.

318
00:23:57.019 --> 00:23:58.686
A man who wants to breathe free.

319
00:23:58.719 --> 00:24:01.686
Spare me the propaganda
bullshit. all right?

320
00:24:01.719 --> 00:24:02.986
I meant your name.

321
00:24:06.119 --> 00:24:07.452
Randall.

322
00:24:07.486 --> 00:24:08.752
Well. Randall.

323
00:24:08.786 --> 00:24:09.986
I don't want your type of freedom.

324
00:24:10.019 --> 00:24:11.652
I don't want anything.

325
00:24:12.919 --> 00:24:17.486
It takes a lot of effort not to be free--

326
00:24:17.519 --> 00:24:20.019
keeping your head down.
holding your tongue.

327
00:24:20.052 --> 00:24:23.786
I'm all for keeping my head
down and my mouth shut.

328
00:24:23.819 --> 00:24:25.786
as long as I get to live.

329
00:24:25.819 --> 00:24:28.519
There's things worth more than
your life. and you know it.

330
00:24:33.452 --> 00:24:35.352
You know where Trudy's sister went.

331
00:24:40.086 --> 00:24:42.419
Don't you?

332
00:24:42.452 --> 00:24:44.652
What do you know about that?

333
00:24:44.686 --> 00:24:46.752
The question is what do you know?

334
00:24:51.786 --> 00:24:54.852
Yeah. you know where she went.

335
00:24:54.886 --> 00:24:56.719
Why don't you tell them?

336
00:25:00.519 --> 00:25:02.652
They'll kill me anyway.

337
00:25:02.686 --> 00:25:03.686
Maybe.

338
00:25:05.152 --> 00:25:08.552
Why don't you tell them
and see what happens?

339
00:25:08.586 --> 00:25:11.619
If you can believe they'll keep their word.

340
00:25:17.819 --> 00:25:19.552
Hey. can I take a break?

341
00:25:21.952 --> 00:25:24.086
- Ten minutes.
- Thank you.

342
00:25:24.119 --> 00:25:25.086
Mm-hmm.

343
00:25:46.519 --> 00:25:49.552
♪ ...maybe so

344
00:25:49.586 --> 00:25:55.086
♪ But in my heart I know

345
00:25:55.119 --> 00:26:00.352
♪ I'll never get old

346
00:26:06.419 --> 00:26:07.886
Hello.

347
00:26:07.919 --> 00:26:09.586
Hello.

348
00:26:13.419 --> 00:26:15.819
I'm. uh. I'm looking for a Bible.

349
00:26:18.419 --> 00:26:19.752
A Bible?

350
00:26:19.786 --> 00:26:23.086
Old Testament. please.

351
00:26:23.119 --> 00:26:24.919
King James translation.

352
00:26:27.552 --> 00:26:29.819
What makes you think I have one of those?

353
00:26:29.852 --> 00:26:31.652
Someone told me you did.

354
00:26:36.052 --> 00:26:37.552
It's not like they're illegal or anything.

355
00:26:37.586 --> 00:26:39.319
Right?

356
00:26:41.886 --> 00:26:43.886
No laws around here.

357
00:26:45.086 --> 00:26:48.019
They may not be illegal. but. uh.

358
00:26:48.052 --> 00:26:50.419
that doesn't exactly make them legal.

359
00:26:50.452 --> 00:26:52.886
if you know what I mean.

360
00:26:52.919 --> 00:26:54.786
Of course.

361
00:26:59.152 --> 00:27:00.819
Do you have one?

362
00:27:03.052 --> 00:27:04.352
Please?

363
00:27:21.752 --> 00:27:22.852
7 marks.

364
00:27:37.552 --> 00:27:38.652
Thank you.

365
00:27:48.852 --> 00:27:51.052
Man: Go. go. go!

366
00:27:51.086 --> 00:27:53.019
Are you all right. Obergruppenführer?

367
00:27:53.052 --> 00:27:54.719
- How's Erich?
- He's in critical condition.

368
00:27:54.752 --> 00:27:57.086
One of the bullets lodged
only 2 inches from his heart.

369
00:27:57.119 --> 00:27:58.619
I'm afraid I have more bad news. sir.

370
00:27:58.652 --> 00:27:59.886
Don't be coy. Lawrence.

371
00:27:59.919 --> 00:28:01.419
It's Hauptaturmführer Lautz.

372
00:28:01.452 --> 00:28:02.486
His vehicle's gone missing.

373
00:28:02.519 --> 00:28:03.886
Missing when?

374
00:28:03.919 --> 00:28:05.720
Last seen crossing the
Pelham Bridge at 8:41.

375
00:28:05.752 --> 00:28:06.952
No sign of him or his driver since.

376
00:28:06.986 --> 00:28:08.652
These were coordinated attacks.

377
00:28:08.686 --> 00:28:10.852
reprisals for the Resistance
leader we killed.

378
00:28:10.886 --> 00:28:12.719
What about the man I apprehended?

379
00:28:12.752 --> 00:28:14.786
A Semite. sir. known as Doc.

380
00:28:14.819 --> 00:28:15.919
Born Jason Meyer.

381
00:28:15.952 --> 00:28:17.886
Parents exterminated Cincinnati Camp.

382
00:28:17.919 --> 00:28:19.852
May 17. 1951.

383
00:28:19.886 --> 00:28:21.086
We wipe them out.

384
00:28:21.119 --> 00:28:22.752
yet they keep coming back like lice.

385
00:28:22.786 --> 00:28:25.552
Lice don't assassinate Nazi officers.

386
00:28:25.586 --> 00:28:26.652
I only meant--

387
00:28:26.686 --> 00:28:27.986
It may reassure you

388
00:28:28.019 --> 00:28:30.419
to liken terrorists to insects.

389
00:28:30.452 --> 00:28:32.786
but they inflicted great
damage on us today.

390
00:28:32.819 --> 00:28:34.119
Never underestimate them.

391
00:28:34.152 --> 00:28:35.919
Yes. Obergruppenführer.

392
00:28:35.952 --> 00:28:38.686
I vary my route every day.

393
00:28:38.719 --> 00:28:41.919
and yet this Semite knew
exactly where to find us.

394
00:28:41.952 --> 00:28:43.952
- How could he. sir?
- I don't know.

395
00:28:45.952 --> 00:28:47.786
But I intend to find out.

396
00:29:05.119 --> 00:29:06.586
Frank. you in there?

397
00:29:14.486 --> 00:29:16.652
Oh. Jesus.

398
00:29:21.652 --> 00:29:22.919
Fuck!

399
00:29:22.952 --> 00:29:26.019
What are you doing? Frank!

400
00:29:26.052 --> 00:29:27.652
Even if you broke the chains.

401
00:29:27.686 --> 00:29:29.419
how do you think you're
going to get out of here?

402
00:29:29.452 --> 00:29:31.752
Fuck!

403
00:29:38.519 --> 00:29:40.086
Was it worth it?

404
00:29:40.119 --> 00:29:44.386
All so you could pass on
that stupid film of yours.

405
00:29:44.419 --> 00:29:46.652
That film can change the world.

406
00:29:46.686 --> 00:29:48.919
Yeah. it certainly changed mine.

407
00:29:48.952 --> 00:29:51.119
Why do you think they torture us?

408
00:29:51.152 --> 00:29:53.119
I got a feeling you're going to tell me.

409
00:29:53.152 --> 00:29:55.486
Because they know that
that film shows the world

410
00:29:55.519 --> 00:29:58.419
not as it is but as it could be.

411
00:29:58.452 --> 00:29:59.852
Yeah. well. in this world.

412
00:29:59.886 --> 00:30:00.986
they flattened D.C.with an A bomb.

413
00:30:01.019 --> 00:30:02.052
How do you people think a film

414
00:30:02.086 --> 00:30:03.419
is going to fight against that?

415
00:30:03.452 --> 00:30:05.452
- "You people"?
- Yeah. you people.

416
00:30:05.486 --> 00:30:06.919
You dead-enders in the Resistance.

417
00:30:06.952 --> 00:30:08.686
How many are you anyway. huh?

418
00:30:08.719 --> 00:30:10.652
What. like seven. ten. 12?

419
00:30:10.686 --> 00:30:13.686
You really think you're going
to defeat the Japanese?

420
00:30:13.719 --> 00:30:15.786
The Nazis?

421
00:30:15.819 --> 00:30:17.586
Of course.

422
00:30:17.619 --> 00:30:19.519
That's not the way it looks from here!

423
00:30:28.552 --> 00:30:31.086
Evil triumphs only when
good men do nothing.

424
00:30:34.952 --> 00:30:36.786
- Hi.
- Hello.

425
00:30:46.586 --> 00:30:47.686
Can I help you find something?

426
00:30:47.719 --> 00:30:49.319
Yeah. Uh...

427
00:30:50.586 --> 00:30:51.819
what do you got for kids?

428
00:30:51.852 --> 00:30:53.752
Kids?

429
00:30:53.786 --> 00:30:56.686
You have something for a boy to read?

430
00:30:56.719 --> 00:30:58.886
How old is this boy?

431
00:30:58.919 --> 00:31:00.586
He's 10.

432
00:31:11.552 --> 00:31:12.819
Here you are.

433
00:31:14.719 --> 00:31:15.986
What's this?

434
00:31:16.019 --> 00:31:17.719
Adventures of Huckleberry Finn.

435
00:31:17.752 --> 00:31:18.919
I've never heard of it.

436
00:31:18.952 --> 00:31:19.986
He'll like it.

437
00:31:20.019 --> 00:31:22.586
- How much?
- 3 marks.

438
00:31:22.619 --> 00:31:25.552
Say. the. uh. gal who just came in here.

439
00:31:25.586 --> 00:31:26.786
what did she buy?

440
00:31:26.819 --> 00:31:28.619
What gal?

441
00:31:28.652 --> 00:31:29.786
The pretty one? You know?

442
00:31:29.819 --> 00:31:31.380
She was just in here a few minutes ago.

443
00:31:33.119 --> 00:31:35.352
I'm sorry. I don’t remember any gal.

444
00:31:39.752 --> 00:31:40.819
Well. thank you.

445
00:31:53.119 --> 00:31:56.419
"...when they shall be afraid
of that which is high.

446
00:31:56.452 --> 00:31:59.652
"and fears shall bein the way.

447
00:31:59.686 --> 00:32:02.552
"and the almond tree shall flourish.

448
00:32:02.586 --> 00:32:04.752
and the grasshopper shall be a burden..."

449
00:32:29.619 --> 00:32:31.352
Come on. Frank.

450
00:32:44.919 --> 00:32:48.019
Frank? Frank. it's me.

451
00:32:48.052 --> 00:32:49.852
Man: Is that Miss Crain?

452
00:33:42.686 --> 00:33:45.119
Ah. Mr. Baynes. good to see you again.

453
00:33:45.152 --> 00:33:46.552
Mr. Tagomi.

454
00:33:46.586 --> 00:33:47.852
- Please.
- Thanks.

455
00:33:53.686 --> 00:33:55.452
I see you’ve brought me something.

456
00:33:55.486 --> 00:33:57.619
Textile samples.

457
00:33:57.652 --> 00:34:00.019
Finest Swedish craftmanship.

458
00:34:00.052 --> 00:34:02.386
Oh!

459
00:34:02.419 --> 00:34:05.319
Our distributors will be delighted.

460
00:34:12.152 --> 00:34:15.119
I trust your visit has been
uneventful. Colonel Wegener.

461
00:34:15.152 --> 00:34:18.552
Until I received your call this afternoon.

462
00:34:18.586 --> 00:34:20.519
Is everything all right
with the Crown Prince?

463
00:34:20.552 --> 00:34:24.452
Yes. His ship will dock
tomorrow morning as scheduled.

464
00:34:24.486 --> 00:34:25.986
Then why have I been called?

465
00:34:26.019 --> 00:34:28.552
Your meeting must be canceled.

466
00:34:28.586 --> 00:34:29.852
Canceled?

467
00:34:29.886 --> 00:34:31.852
Ambassador Reiss came to see me today.

468
00:34:31.886 --> 00:34:33.952
along with an S.S.officer-- Diels.

469
00:34:33.986 --> 00:34:35.452
I know who he is.

470
00:34:35.486 --> 00:34:37.786
He reports directly to Heydrich in Berlin.

471
00:34:37.819 --> 00:34:39.686
They're determined to find a woman

472
00:34:39.719 --> 00:34:42.919
smuggling a film destined for
the Man In the High Castle.

473
00:34:42.952 --> 00:34:44.719
What does that have to do with us?

474
00:34:44.752 --> 00:34:46.952
We did not inform them about the smuggler.

475
00:34:46.986 --> 00:34:48.352
and yet they knew.

476
00:34:48.386 --> 00:34:50.052
It's clear your Nazi colleagues

477
00:34:50.086 --> 00:34:52.619
have infiltrated our security services.

478
00:34:52.652 --> 00:34:54.519
It's hardly a surprise.

479
00:34:54.552 --> 00:34:56.652
To this degree the risk is too great.

480
00:34:58.619 --> 00:35:00.352
Is that what your sticks tell you?

481
00:35:00.386 --> 00:35:03.119
Do you knowhow long I've worked

482
00:35:03.152 --> 00:35:04.719
to organize this meeting?

483
00:35:04.752 --> 00:35:06.652
The risk I've taken to come here?

484
00:35:06.686 --> 00:35:08.819
- I understand.
- I don't think you do.

485
00:35:08.852 --> 00:35:11.552
The Führer is ill. and he could die.

486
00:35:11.586 --> 00:35:13.519
and when he does.

487
00:35:13.552 --> 00:35:16.986
there will be a war between
our empires. Mr. Tagomi.

488
00:35:17.019 --> 00:35:19.419
There will be another time.

489
00:35:19.452 --> 00:35:21.819
I cannot travel twice on a
forged Swedish passport.

490
00:35:21.852 --> 00:35:22.986
I'll be shot.

491
00:35:23.019 --> 00:35:25.552
Give me the secrets.

492
00:35:25.586 --> 00:35:26.819
Let me deliver them.

493
00:35:28.052 --> 00:35:29.752
And if that oracle of yours

494
00:35:29.786 --> 00:35:32.552
tells you not to go through with it?

495
00:35:37.886 --> 00:35:40.586
You said it yourself. Mr. Tagomi.

496
00:35:40.619 --> 00:35:43.686
Destiny is in the hands of men.

497
00:35:43.719 --> 00:35:47.919
I'm afraid this time that means me.

498
00:36:10.886 --> 00:36:12.752
Mrs. Crothers. isn't it?

499
00:36:12.786 --> 00:36:13.786
Yes.

500
00:36:13.819 --> 00:36:14.919
I'm Chief Inspector Kido.

501
00:36:14.952 --> 00:36:16.352
Thank you for coming in.

502
00:36:18.686 --> 00:36:21.719
Well. we weren't given a choice. actually.

503
00:36:21.752 --> 00:36:23.786
We appreciate your cooperation.

504
00:36:23.819 --> 00:36:27.952
This must be John.

505
00:36:27.986 --> 00:36:29.552
And Emily.

506
00:36:31.952 --> 00:36:33.619
We'll need a picture. please.

507
00:36:40.619 --> 00:36:42.086
What's this about. Inspector?

508
00:36:42.119 --> 00:36:43.652
Oh. it's a formality.

509
00:36:43.686 --> 00:36:45.652
We're reviewing the
records of your brother.

510
00:36:45.686 --> 00:36:47.386
Frank? Is he okay?

511
00:36:47.419 --> 00:36:48.952
He's fine. Please.

512
00:36:48.986 --> 00:36:51.586
we have a very comfortable
waiting room down the hall.

513
00:36:51.619 --> 00:36:53.686
I'll be with you as soon as possible.

514
00:36:53.719 --> 00:36:55.519
How long will we be here?

515
00:36:55.552 --> 00:36:56.786
Not long.

516
00:36:56.819 --> 00:36:57.819
I hope.

517
00:36:57.852 --> 00:36:59.486
Please follow me.

518
00:37:27.019 --> 00:37:29.086
Mom. may we watch TV?

519
00:37:29.119 --> 00:37:31.652
Yes. Yes. of course.

520
00:37:31.686 --> 00:37:33.986
Please. make yourselves comfortable.

521
00:37:34.019 --> 00:37:35.952
Oh. Thank you.

522
00:38:04.952 --> 00:38:06.819
It's a beautiful family.

523
00:38:14.552 --> 00:38:16.786
W-What are you going to do?

524
00:38:16.819 --> 00:38:19.319
You've heard of Zyklon D?

525
00:38:24.119 --> 00:38:27.119
It's a gas. It's a gas.

526
00:38:27.152 --> 00:38:30.119
It is much improved since the war.

527
00:38:30.152 --> 00:38:33.919
Odorless and fast-acting.

528
00:38:35.952 --> 00:38:38.419
They'll fall asleep and never wake up.

529
00:38:43.719 --> 00:38:45.919
J-Just let them go.

530
00:38:50.386 --> 00:38:52.019
Where is Juliana Crain?

531
00:38:55.486 --> 00:38:58.952
We know Miss Walker met
her at an herb shop.

532
00:38:58.986 --> 00:39:02.819
We know she gave her the film.

533
00:39:02.852 --> 00:39:06.119
We even know she took
it to the Neutral Zone.

534
00:39:06.152 --> 00:39:09.452
We believe she was at the bus terminal.

535
00:39:09.486 --> 00:39:13.086
So all you need to tell us
is which bus she boarded.

536
00:39:15.786 --> 00:39:17.786
Where is Juliana Crain?

537
00:39:22.986 --> 00:39:25.519
Is it worth dying for her?

538
00:39:27.619 --> 00:39:29.686
A woman who thinks you are a failure?

539
00:39:30.986 --> 00:39:33.052
Who doesn't even love you?

540
00:39:33.086 --> 00:39:34.952
Randall: It's a lie. Frank.

541
00:39:34.986 --> 00:39:36.086
Stay strong!

542
